25/02/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH and Serbia-Montenegro must fulfil their commitments to the UN war crimes tribunal in order to open the way for the two countries' European future, Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic said Thursday (24 February) in Sarajevo. 
Together with BiH Presidency Chairman Borislav Paravac, Marovic presided over the 5th session of the Interstate Council for Co-operation between BiH and Serbia-Montenegro. 
The two leaders said relations between their countries are good, especially in the economic field. 
They agreed that their security institutions should intensify contacts in order to help both countries meet obligations to the tribunal, as well as to tackle organized crime and trafficking.
On the sidelines of the meeting, the foreign affairs and justice ministers of the two countries signed six co-operation accords relating to border crossings between BiH and Serbia-Montenegro, the border traffic regime and legal collaboration in criminal matters. 
(FENA, PBS, RTRS - 24/02/05)
